links.title: Buy the Dip on Netflix Shares, Analysts Advise
links.description: Here's Wall Street's general advice on shares: Buy the dip. For the second straight quarter, Netflix (ticker: NFLX) investors are selling off post-earnings-and on the very same data point. When the streaming video giant reported June quarter results Tuesday, the company projected September quarter net new subscriber growth of 2.5 million, well below both the double-digit gains of the year's first two quarters and previous Street estimates.

links.title: Netflix subscription gains screech lower as pandemic wears on, stock falls 5%
links.description: Netflix Inc. reported a dramatic slowdown in new subscribers Tuesday and widely missed earnings expectations, sending shares on a plunge in after-hours trading. Netflix reported 2.2 million net new subscribers in its third quarter, after two consecutive quarters topping the 10 million mark amid shelter-in-place orders related to the COVID-19 pandemic.
